# Company Brief

**The House We Built** is a media company that helps families
build intentional homes.

**Trellis** is our software — the operating system for families.

## What we do

We make the systems and stories families use to live on purpose.

The House We Built publishes essays, podcasts, and frameworks
about family rhythm, partnership, parenting, and stewardship. Our
audience is intentional parents aged 30-45 who are tired of
winging the family thing and want a blueprint.

Trellis is the app that turns that philosophy into daily practice.
Eleven pillars of household leadership. One shared dashboard for
both parents. An AI family steward named Cy that reads the
patterns parents are too tired to notice. Age-appropriate views
for every kid.

Families subscribe to Trellis for $29/month. All pillars included.
Both parents. Every kid. All content from The House We Built.

## Why it exists

The modern family has no operating system. Work got Slack and
Notion. Fitness got Whoop and Oura. Money got Monarch and YNAB.
The family — the most important institution in the world — runs
on memory, sticky notes, and group texts.

Sixty-two percent of couples argue about scheduling, chores, or
money every week. The average mother carries 40 hours of mental
load per week on family logistics. One in three marriages ends in
divorce, and the number one cited reason is chronic financial and
logistical stress.

The chaos isn't a personality problem. It's a systems problem.
Nobody has built the system.

We're building it.

